when you practice

00:30:27.800 --> 00:30:32.090 align:middle line:90%
mindfulness and concentration.

00:30:32.090 --> 00:30:38.840 align:middle line:84%
>> The human brain is a very
fascinating, three pound, soft,

00:30:38.840 --> 00:30:41.100 align:middle line:84%
jello-like organ
inside the skull,

00:30:41.100 --> 00:30:44.630 align:middle line:84%
which is more complicated than
anything else in the universe.

00:30:44.630 --> 00:30:46.280 align:middle line:84%
We have three
parts to our brain.

00:30:46.280 --> 00:30:49.560 align:middle line:84%
The first part of the brain
is called the midbrain.

00:30:49.560 --> 00:30:52.250 align:middle line:84%
It's also called
the reptilian brain.

00:30:52.250 --> 00:30:56.600 align:middle line:84%
The reptilian brain evolved
300 million years ago.

00:30:56.600 --> 00:30:58.730 align:middle line:84%
The reason it's called
the reptilian brain

00:30:58.730 --> 00:31:00.310 align:middle line:84%
is that when you go
next to a reptile

00:31:00.310 --> 00:31:03.440 align:middle line:84%
and you either make a sudden
movement or a sudden noise,

00:31:03.440 --> 00:31:06.080 align:middle line:84%
if you're very close, the
reptile will attack you.

00:31:06.080 --> 00:31:09.560 align:middle line:84%
If you're a little further
away, it will slither away.

00:31:09.560 --> 00:31:12.080 align:middle line:84%
This is the beginning of what
we call the fight or flight

00:31:12.080 --> 00:31:16.460 align:middle line:84%
response, and this then
becomes, in our society,

00:31:16.460 --> 00:31:18.500 align:middle line:90%
the stress response.

00:31:18.500 --> 00:31:20.810 align:middle line:84%
You're not trying to save
yourself from a saber tooth

00:31:20.810 --> 00:31:24.450 align:middle line:84%
tiger, but somebody
blows the horn at you

00:31:24.450 --> 00:31:26.625 align:middle line:84%
or somebody says
something that triggers,

00:31:26.625 --> 00:31:30.470 align:middle line:84%
and all the hurt
pushes your buttons

00:31:30.470 --> 00:31:32.600 align:middle line:90%
and you attack or you run.

00:31:32.600 --> 00:31:35.510 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes you're not
attacking or running,

00:31:35.510 --> 00:31:38.690 align:middle line:84%
but you feel frustrated and
that raises your blood pressure.

00:31:38.690 --> 00:31:39.800 align:middle line:90%
Heart rate goes up.

00:31:39.800 --> 00:31:41.960 align:middle line:90%
Cortisol goes up.

00:31:41.960 --> 00:31:45.230 align:middle line:90%
Adrenaline goes up.

00:31:45.230 --> 00:31:50.120 align:middle line:84%
Stress is linked to almost every
major epidemic of civilization.

00:31:50.120 --> 00:31:53.780 align:middle line:84%
Whether it is cancer or
heart disease or infections

00:31:53.780 --> 00:31:59.540 align:middle line:84%
or premature aging, sudden death
from cardiovascular illness,

00:31:59.540 --> 00:32:01.380 align:middle line:90%
all linked to stress.

00:32:01.380 --> 00:32:05.330 align:middle line:84%
And this is what the stress
is, the midbrain reacting as it

00:32:05.330 --> 00:32:08.480 align:middle line:90%
has done for 300 million years.

00:32:08.480 --> 00:32:10.180 align:middle line:84%
Then the second
part of your brain

00:32:10.180 --> 00:32:12.350 align:middle line:84%
is called the
limbic brain, which

00:32:12.350 --> 00:32:16.370 align:middle line:90%
is about 100 million years old.

00:32:16.370 --> 00:32:17.930 align:middle line:90%
This is our emotional brain.

00:32:17.930 --> 00:32:20.720 align:middle line:84%
So we have basically
five emotions,

00:32:20.720 --> 00:32:23.300 align:middle line:84%
and everything else
is a variant of them.

00:32:23.300 --> 00:32:27.935 align:middle line:84%
The first emotion is happiness,
so love, compassion, kindness.

00:32:27.935 --> 00:32:29.055 align:middle line:90%
They all fit in happiness.

00:32:29.055 --> 00:32:32.100 align:middle line:84%
It makes you happy
when you're in love.

00:32:32.100 --> 00:32:34.740 align:middle line:90%
The second emotion is sadness.

00:32:34.740 --> 00:32:37.270 align:middle line:84%
The third is anger
and hostility.

00:32:37.270 --> 00:32:40.020 align:middle line:90%
The fourth is fear.

00:32:40.020 --> 00:32:44.910 align:middle line:84%
The fifth is shame,
and what do you call--

00:32:44.910 --> 00:32:48.210 align:middle line:90%
guilt. And every other emotion--

00:32:48.210 --> 00:32:51.680 align:middle line:84%
disgust, jealousy--
is a variant of these.

00:32:51.680 --> 00:32:54.300 align:middle line:84%
Now, it turns out that
when you're happy--

00:32:54.300 --> 00:32:56.380 align:middle line:84%
and this happens
only in mammals.

00:32:56.380 --> 00:32:59.280 align:middle line:84%
Reptiles don't have
a emotional life.

00:32:59.280 --> 00:33:03.540 align:middle line:84%
But all mammals
form social groups.

00:33:03.540 --> 00:33:06.540 align:middle line:90%
All mammals nurture their young.

00:33:06.540 --> 00:33:09.730 align:middle line:84%
Believe it or not,
all mammals sing.

00:33:09.730 --> 00:33:14.820 align:middle line:84%
All mammals play, and
this is the experience

00:33:14.820 --> 00:33:18.510 align:middle line:84%
of what we call love
that occurs immediately

00:33:18.510 --> 00:33:22.290 align:middle line:84%
after a child is born and even
in the anticipation of a child.

00:33:22.290 --> 00:33:24.390 align:middle line:84%
And it turns out that
our feedback loops,

00:33:24.390 --> 00:33:27.120 align:middle line:84%
self-repair mechanisms
in the body,

00:33:27.120 --> 00:33:31.320 align:middle line:84%
are matured and
come into existence

00:33:31.320 --> 00:33:34.590 align:middle line:84%
as a result of the
experience of love.

00:33:34.590 --> 00:33:39.090 align:middle line:84%
If we don't have that attention,
affection, appreciation,

00:33:39.090 --> 00:33:43.590 align:middle line:84%
cooing cuddling,
kissing, touching,

00:33:43.590 --> 00:33:46.470 align:middle line:84%
the dance between an
adult and a child,

00:33:46.470 --> 00:33:51.600 align:middle line:84%
which is eye movements, facial
expressions, body language,

00:33:51.600 --> 00:33:52.875 align:middle line:90%
voice tone--

00:33:52.875 --> 00:33:55.620 align:middle line:84%
a child doesn't understand
rational language

00:33:55.620 --> 00:33:58.790 align:middle line:84%
but understands that
language from day one, OK?

00:33:58.790 --> 00:34:02.070 align:middle line:84%
And that is it responsible
for the maturation

00:34:02.070 --> 00:34:05.460 align:middle line:84%
of self-repair mechanisms
and self-regulation.

00:34:05.460 --> 00:34:10.560 align:middle line:84%
If you're deprived of that,
you will be a sick adult.

00:34:10.560 --> 00:34:13.350 align:middle line:84%
When you grow up,
your everything

00:34:13.350 --> 00:34:15.540 align:middle line:84%
will be affected because
the self-repair is linked

00:34:15.540 --> 00:34:17.909 align:middle line:84%
to hormone levels,
body temperature

00:34:17.909 --> 00:34:21.540 align:middle line:84%
regulation, autonomic
responses, everything

00:34:21.540 --> 00:34:23.790 align:middle line:90%
that keeps the body healthy.

00:34:23.790 --> 00:34:25.500 align:middle line:90%
That's our limbic brain.

00:34:25.500 --> 00:34:29.010 align:middle line:84%
Most people have
dysfunctional limbic systems,

00:34:29.010 --> 00:34:32.650 align:middle line:84%
in that they're resentful
or angry about the past.

00:34:32.650 --> 00:34:36.590 align:middle line:84%
They're anticipating
something fear in the future.

00:34:36.590 --> 00:34:38.610 align:middle line:84%
They have shame and
guilt about things

00:34:38.610 --> 00:34:40.960 align:middle line:84%
that they regret that
they shouldn't have done.

00:34:40.960 --> 00:34:44.630 align:middle line:84%
And as a result, you
their biological systems

00:34:44.630 --> 00:34:47.969 align:middle line:90%
are totally disrupted.

00:34:47.969 --> 00:34:50.790 align:middle line:84%
But on the other hand, when you
have what the Buddhists call

00:34:50.790 --> 00:34:59.820 align:middle line:84%
loving-kindness, joy, peace
of mind, and compassion--

00:34:59.820 --> 00:35:02.760 align:middle line:84%
the Buddhists call them
divine attributes--

00:35:02.760 --> 00:35:08.790 align:middle line:84%
in that state your body's the
best it could possibly be, OK?

00:35:08.790 --> 00:35:11.040 align:middle line:84%
So that's your limbic
brain, and then you

00:35:11.040 --> 00:35:13.620 align:middle line:84%
have this cortical
brain, which is huge,

00:35:13.620 --> 00:35:15.870 align:middle line:84%
which is only four
million years old.

00:35:15.870 --> 00:35:19.410 align:middle line:84%
The cortical brain
houses rationality.

00:35:19.410 --> 00:35:24.090 align:middle line:84%
It's also responsible for
orchestrating intention,

00:35:24.090 --> 00:35:26.940 align:middle line:84%
and it seems this
is the place we

00:35:26.940 --> 00:35:32.010 align:middle line:84%
use for imagination and insight
and intuition and creativity.

00:35:32.010 --> 00:35:33.060 align:middle line:90%
Now, here's the secret.

00:35:33.060 --> 00:35:35.490 align:middle line:84%
In mindfulness, what
you can learn to do--

00:35:35.490 --> 00:35:38.850 align:middle line:84%
and this is proven
scientifically--

00:35:38.850 --> 00:35:44.010 align:middle line:84%
you can totally
override your midbrain.

00:35:44.010 --> 00:35:46.710 align:middle line:84%
So a person like Thich
Nhat Hahn, for example,

00:35:46.710 --> 00:35:50.670 align:middle line:84%
for all practical
purposes, his midbrain

00:35:50.670 --> 00:35:53.790 align:middle line:90%
is no longer functioning.

00:35:53.790 --> 00:35:58.980 align:middle line:84%
You can't get him to be angry
or feel hostility or resentful.

00:35:58.980 --> 00:36:04.290 align:middle line:84%
He's just-- he's quieted it
through mindfulness practice.

00:36:04.290 --> 00:36:08.070 align:middle line:84%
And if you sustain that
mindfulness practice,

00:36:08.070 --> 00:36:12.270 align:middle line:84%
you feel so connected
that spontaneously,

00:36:12.270 --> 00:36:15.510 align:middle line:84%
your limbic system starts to get
activated so you nurture only

00:36:15.510 --> 00:36:18.740 align:middle line:84%
healthy emotions, like
love, compassion, joy, et

00:36:18.740 --> 00:36:22.050 align:middle line:84%
cetera, that come from
that place of equanimity.

00:36:22.050 --> 00:36:24.960 align:middle line:84%
So you're using
your cortical brain

00:36:24.960 --> 00:36:31.560 align:middle line:84%
to, first of all, override
the detrimental, destructive

00:36:31.560 --> 00:36:33.240 align:middle line:84%
tendencies of the
midbrain, which

00:36:33.240 --> 00:36:37.680 align:middle line:84%
is no longer relevant
in the modern society,

00:36:37.680 --> 00:36:39.720 align:middle line:84%
and you're also activating
the limbic brain

00:36:39.720 --> 00:36:41.130 align:middle line:90%
for nurturing relationships.

00:36:41.130 --> 00:36:44.640 align:middle line:84%
You're literally rewiring
your nervous system.

00:36:44.640 --> 00:36:47.220 align:middle line:84%
In neuroscience, we say
neurons that fire together

00:36:47.220 --> 00:36:48.390 align:middle line:90%
wire together.

00:36:48.390 --> 00:36:50.820 align:middle line:84%
You're an intelligent
human being

00:36:50.820 --> 00:36:55.170 align:middle line:84%
who has subdued the
reptilian brain, who

00:36:55.170 --> 00:36:57.990 align:middle line:84%
knows how to activate
the limbic brain, who

00:36:57.990 --> 00:37:00.450 align:middle line:84%
knows how to
self-repair and heal,

00:37:00.450 --> 00:37:04.890 align:middle line:84%
who has more intuition, insight,
imagination, creativity,

00:37:04.890 --> 00:37:05.970 align:middle line:90%
and choice making.

00:37:05.970 --> 00:37:08.670 align:middle line:84%
It's a new evolution
of the human species.

00:37:08.670 --> 00:37:13.410 align:middle line:84%
>> Imagine a situation where
your day was going fine.

00:37:13.410 --> 00:37:16.620 align:middle line:84%
Someone looked at
you in a way that you

00:37:16.620 --> 00:37:19.830 align:middle line:84%
imagined was attacking,
accusatory, or judgmental,

00:37:19.830 --> 00:37:21.270 align:middle line:90%
and you get angry.

00:37:21.270 --> 00:37:25.200 align:middle line:84%
Now, whereas in the past, you
might have become very angry

00:37:25.200 --> 00:37:29.750 align:middle line:84%
and disregulated and done
behaviors that got you

00:37:29.750 --> 00:37:31.750 align:middle line:84%
into more trouble, whether
it's drugs or alcohol

00:37:31.750 --> 00:37:35.110 align:middle line:84%
or whatever it is, what
you do with mindfulness

00:37:35.110 --> 00:37:39.340 align:middle line:84%
is you pay attention to what
is in this present moment.

00:37:39.340 --> 00:37:40.690 align:middle line:90%
What happened?

00:37:40.690 --> 00:37:42.790 align:middle line:90%
Describe what happened.

00:37:42.790 --> 00:37:48.370 align:middle line:84%
The person looked at me
from the side of their face.

00:37:48.370 --> 00:37:50.440 align:middle line:90%
They seem to have a frown.

00:37:50.440 --> 00:37:52.040 align:middle line:84%
Whatever it is that
you're describing,

00:37:52.040 --> 00:37:56.890 align:middle line:84%
you're describing what is,
not what you imagine it to be.

00:37:56.890 --> 00:38:01.540 align:middle line:84%
And by doing that, it
gives you a fighting chance

00:38:01.540 --> 00:38:04.040 align:middle line:84%
of staying a lot calmer than
what you could have gone,

00:38:04.040 --> 00:38:05.800 align:middle line:84%
because once you
start describing,

00:38:05.800 --> 00:38:08.090 align:middle line:84%
then you also have the
opportunity to be curious.

00:38:08.090 --> 00:38:10.120 align:middle line:84%
You might ask the
person, hey, why did you

00:38:10.120 --> 00:38:11.080 align:middle line:90%
give me that bad look?

00:38:11.080 --> 00:38:12.700 align:middle line:90%
He say, what bad look?

00:38:12.700 --> 00:38:16.350 align:middle line:84%
I have gastric problems from the
burrito I had at lunch today,

00:38:16.350 --> 00:38:18.080 align:middle line:90%
and maybe I was grimacing.

00:38:18.080 --> 00:38:18.880 align:middle line:90%
I mean, who knows?

00:38:18.880 --> 00:38:21.497 align:middle line:84%
>> We should be
